Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula will be in Polokwane in Limpopo to meet with traffic officials. JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula will be in Polokwane in Limpopo on Tuesday to meet with traffic officials. This follows a horrific Youth Day crash, between a bus and a taxi, that claimed 24 lives on the R81 in Maphalle. READ: 24 killed in crash outside Tzaneen A number of people were also injured and taken to hospital. Mbalula is expected to brief media after his meeting with officials. 